title: FATAL output
content:
Does anybody understand what this means?:

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20100203142256im_/http:/typophile.com/files/FATAL_4526.gif)

I assume it means multiple glyphs are mapped to 0021, but I can't figure what they are.

When viewed in unicode I only see the exclam. Any help would be gratefully received.

Thanks in advance.
author: Nick Cooke

comments.content:
Try looking in Index mode rather than unicode. Look for a glyph named \_33.

André

Thanks André, I found it.

Nick Cooke
